    title Privacy Policy - Hanzo
  body
    h1 Privacy Policy
    section#overview
      h2 Overview & Definitions
      p
        | “You” refers to visitors of our websites, users of our Services (“User”), or a customer of a User (“Customer”).
        | “Personal Data” identifies You as an individual and includes contact details, financial and transaction Data, demographic information, and other Personal Data.
        | “Other Data” encompasses browser and device data, transaction data, cookie and tracking technology data, behavioral data, and company data. It also includes data from third-party sources and information collected from customer interactions.

    section#data-collection
      h2 Data Collection
      p
        | a. Directly from You: When creating a Hanzo account, making transactions, using forms, or receiving emails, surveys, and other online interactions.
        | b. Recording Interactions: Technologies like cookies, web beacons, and callbacks.
        | c. Third Parties: Financial or marketing partners, affiliates, and service providers.

    section#usage-of-data
      h2 Usage of Data
      p
        | Personal Data: To provide Services, detect fraud, mitigate loss, promote and improve products, enhance customer experience, personalize content, comply with legal obligations, and engage in other legitimate interests.
        | Other Data: As permitted by law and contractual commitments, including internal analytics, market research, and product development.

    section#disclosure-of-data
      h2 Disclosure of Data
      p
        | To Hanzo Affiliates and Service Providers: Sharing with trusted parties for processing, analysis, and business support.
        | To Users, Authorized Third Parties: In accordance with user agreements and authorization.
        | For Safety, Legal Purposes, and Law Enforcement: Compliance with legal requests, protection of rights, property, and safety of Hanzo and others.

    section#security
      h2 Security
      p
        | Utilizing reasonable measures, industry-standard technologies, and best practices to protect Data. Regular security assessments and updates are conducted to safeguard information integrity.

    section#advertising
      h2 Advertising
      p
        | Use of third-party companies and technologies for targeted advertising. Collaboration with advertising networks and service providers. Opt-out options available, with details provided in our Cookie Policy.

    section#choice-and-access
      h2 Choice and Access
      p
        | Options for electronic communications and access to Your Personal Data. Opportunities to review, correct, or delete information. Consultation with our support team at support@hanzo.ai.

    section#retention-period
      h2 Retention Period
      p
        | Retention in compliance with obligations and laws. Determination of retention periods based on legal requirements, business needs, and individual preferences.

    section#use-by-minors
      h2 Use by Minors
      p
        | Services not directed to individuals under 13. No intentional collection or solicitation of personal information from minors. Prompt deletion of any unintentionally collected data.

    section#jurisdiction
      h2 Jurisdiction & Cross-Border Transfer
      p
        | Global services with protections for cross-border transfers. Compliance with applicable laws and regulations. Utilization of mechanisms like standard contractual clauses.

    section#hanzo-data-processor
      h2 Hanzo as a Data Processor
      p
        | Collection and use in accordance with User agreements and instructions. Coordination with data controllers to ensure lawful processing.

    section#updates-and-notifications
      h2 Updates and Notifications
      p
        | Periodic updates with prominent notices or direct notifications. Revisions communicated through email, website notifications, or other appropriate channels.

    section#dispute-resolution
      h2 Dispute Resolution and Legal Compliance
      p
        | Hanzo maintains mechanisms for dispute resolution in line with legal regulations. Users with concerns or complaints can contact the designated authorities or Hanzo directly at support@hanzo.ai, and appropriate action will be taken to resolve issues.

    section#age-restrictions
      h2 Age Restrictions and Compliance
      p
        | Hanzo complies with legal age restrictions and does not knowingly collect or process data from minors without parental consent. Verification measures, monitoring, and reporting are in place to ensure compliance with age-related laws.

    section#sustainability-and-ethics
      h2 Sustainability and Ethical AI Practices
      p
        | Hanzo adheres to ethical AI principles and strives to maintain sustainability in its operations. This includes responsible data handling, bias mitigation, ethical guidelines, social responsibility, and environmental considerations in its technology practices.

    section#contact-information
      h2 Contact Information and Customer Support
      p
        | Hanzo provides clear contact information and channels for customer support. Inquiries, requests, or concerns related to data privacy and AI practices can be addressed through designated avenues at support@hanzo.ai, and prompt responses will be provided.

    section#integration-with-systems
      h2 Integration with Other Systems and Services
      p
        | Hanzo integrates with various other systems and services as necessary for its operations. Users are informed of these integrations, and the corresponding data handling is conducted in accordance with privacy laws and regulations. Agreements with third-party providers are maintained to ensure compliance.

    section#ai-transparency
      h2 Artificial Intelligence Transparency
      p
        | Transparency in AI practices is a priority for Hanzo. Details regarding the algorithms used, data processing, decision-making, ethical considerations, and algorithmic accountability are available to users, promoting trust and understanding of AI functionalities.

    section#content-moderation
      h2 Content Moderation and User Behavior
      p
        | Hanzo implements content moderation to ensure a safe and respectful user environment. Guidelines are set for user behavior, and measures are taken to enforce compliance with community standards, including the removal of inappropriate content.

    section#accessibility
      h2 Accessibility and Inclusion Practices
      p
        | Hanzo emphasizes accessibility and inclusion in its services. Efforts are made to accommodate diverse needs, languages, abilities, and cultures, and mechanisms are in place to ensure that all users have equitable access to AI-driven offerings.

    section#retention-and-deletion
      h2 Retention and Deletion of Data
      p
        | Hanzo adheres to legal requirements regarding data retention and deletion. Data is kept only for as long as necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, including legal, business, or tax purposes, and deletion processes comply with relevant laws and regulations.

    section#company-information
      h2 Company Information
      p Hanzo, Inc.
      p 1824 S Fairfax
      p Los Angeles, CA

    section#international-compliance
      h2 International Compliance and Data Protection
      p
        | United States and Europe: Hanzo complies with applicable laws including GDPR in Europe. Users within the European Economic Area have specific rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Consent for processing must be explicit and can be withdrawn at any time. To exercise these rights, please contact our Data Protection Officer at support@hanzo.ai.
        | United Kingdom: Compliance is maintained with UK-specific laws, including the UK Data Protection Act. Adherence to principles of data processing, ensuring lawful, fair, and transparent processing, and respecting individuals' rights concerning their data. Any concerns or requests related to your data may be directed to our UK representative at support@hanzo.ai.
        | Canada: In accordance with Canada's Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA), consent is obtained for the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data. Information will only be used in ways that a reasonable person would expect. For more details or to opt-out, please contact our Canadian representative at support@hanzo.ai.
        | Australia: We adhere to the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) under the Privacy Act 1988, outlining the reason for data collection and how it is used. For inquiries or requests related to your data under Australian law, please contact our Australian representative at support@hanzo.ai.
        | Hong Kong: Hanzo follows the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance (PDPO) in Hong Kong. This includes limitations on data collection and use, and provisions regarding direct marketing and automated decision-making. To exercise your rights under Hong Kong law, please contact our Hong Kong representative at support@hanzo.ai.
        | Singapore: In compliance with the Personal Data Protection Act 2012 (PDPA) in Singapore, we are clear about how and why personal data is collected, used, or disclosed. Measures are in place to protect the data against unauthorized access. To inquire about your data under Singaporean law, please contact our Singapore representative at support@hanzo.ai.

